The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 New software to judge umpires

Mumbai: The BCCI is planning to introduce a software in the system of video recording of domestic matches to help them assess the performance of Indian umpires on a regular basis. 

The BCCIs umpires committee met here on Monday and was given a demonstration by two computer experts, who have developed the software. 

The software will enable us to assess the performance of the umpires in various matches, said BCCIs joint secretary M.P. Pandove. (PTI) 




